The most aesthetically pleasing installation was a custom built radiator
that fit inside a spare tire cover. Mounted on the nose of a bus, it was
backed by an electric fan. IIRC, the plumbing was pretty complex, too,
to prevent 'air locks'...Not a simple thermo-syphon system , at all...

